The Italian National Day was celebratedÂ at the Italian ambassadorial residence in Muthaiga, Nairobi, on June 4. Ambassadors, diplomats, politicians and businessmen graced the afternoon garden reception, which was hosted by Italian Ambassador Mauro Massoni and his wife Olga Massoni. The guest of honour was Foreign Affairs Africa and AU director Ambassador Purity Muhindi. The ambassador presented the ''Knight of the Star of Italy'' award to Italian nationals Father Geraldo Martinelli and Sister Michelina Bora, from the sisters and fathers of the order of La Consolata, for their endless commitment to helping the poor and the needy in Kenya through charity.